                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable H</hi> 89.) I went after the prisoner, and found him at his lodging, at No. 10, Charles-street, Mile-end—I found these articles there—the prisoner said he did not steal the irons, but took them in lieu of some wages that Mr. Salmon owed him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I took them, but not with intent to steal them—I worked with him for 7<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. a-week, from seven o'clock in the morning till eleven or twelve at night, and having got work at a shop I had every thing requisite except these irons—I took them, but I meant to bring them back—the officer came and took me when I was nearly at the finish of my work.</p>
